Variance Components

Adding sires to the data

Convert sire column to factor

Simplify computations with a balanced dataset

ANOVA

            Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value  Pr(>F)   
Sire         2 2651.6  1325.8   13.68 0.00581 **
Residuals    6  581.3    96.9                   
---
Signif. codes:  0 *** 0.001 ** 0.01 * 0.05 . 0.1   1

What is the variance of the sire effect? Use the fact that

\[E(MSQ_R) = \sigma_e^2\] Hence \(\widehat{\sigma_e^2} = MSQ_R = 96.8888889\).

Furthermore

\[E(MSQ_S) = n_S * \sigma_S^2 + \sigma_e^2 \]

Hence

\[\widehat{\sigma_S^2} = \frac{MSQ_S - MSQ_R}{n_S} = \frac{1325.7777778 - 96.8888889}{3}\]
